HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 227
BY REPRESENTATIVE ILLG
A RESOLUTION
To commend Young Marine Sergeant Major Valerie Huete on being named Division 4
Young Marine of the Year and to recognize her exemplary leadership, academic
achievement, and service.
WHEREAS, the Young Marines is a national youth leadership and service program
dedicated to developing disciplined, drug-free, and responsible citizens through leadership
training, community service, and education; and
WHEREAS, the organization serves approximately seven thousand youth members
across the United States and is divided into six geographic divisions; the divisions each
select a Division Young Marine of the Year based on leadership, academic performance,
physical fitness, and community involvement; and
WHEREAS, Young Marine Sergeant Major Valerie Huete is a resident of River
Ridge, Louisiana, and member of the Jefferson Parish Sheriff's Office Young Marines unit;
she has been selected as the Division 4 Young Marine of the Year, which is one of the
highest distinctions within the program; and
WHEREAS, this honor places her among the top six Young Marines out of
approximately seven thousand participants in the United States and reflects her exceptional
character, leadership, and commitment to service; she competed against top Young Marines
from across multiple states within Division 4, including Louisiana, Texas, Oklahoma,
Arkansas, and Mississippi; and
WHEREAS, Valerie Huete is a student at Patrick F. Taylor Science and Technology
Academy in Jefferson Parish, which is a highly regarded academic institution known for its
rigorous curriculum and emphasis on science, technology, and leadership development; her
academic success, combined with her participation in extracurricular and athletic activities,
demonstrates a well-rounded dedication to excellence; and
