WHEREAS, Sergeant Major Huete has demonstrated leadership, mentored fellow
Young Marines, and served her community with distinction throughout her time in the
Young Marines program; she exemplifies the core values of honor, courage, and
commitment; and
WHEREAS, Sergeant Major Huete has received steadfast support and guidance from
her parents, Darren and Vanessa Huete, who have been instrumental in her success; she has
also benefitted from the mentorship, training, and commitment of the dedicated adult
volunteers and leaders of the Young Marines program, including the Jefferson Parish
Sheriff's Office Young Marines unit and Unit Commander Tammy Williams; and
WHEREAS, Sergeant Major Huete's achievements bring great pride to her family,
Patrick F. Taylor Science and Technology Academy, the Jefferson Parish Sheriff's Office
Young Marines unit, the citizens of Jefferson Parish, and the state of Louisiana; it is fitting
to recognize her efforts as her fellow citizens look forward to her continued success and
future contributions to her community and nation.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Young Marine Sergeant Major Valerie
Huete on being named Division 4 Young Marine of the Year; does hereby recognize her as
one of the top young leaders in the nation; and does hereby extend its sincere appreciation
to her parents and family for their encouragement and support and to the adult leaders and
volunteers of the Young Marines program for their dedication to developing future leaders.
